.TH MS1_PEAKTABLE 1 2026-6月 "" "Export peakstable data from the XIC rawdata files"
.SH NAME
ms1_peaktable \- ms1_peaktable(files, mzbins,
    <i>mzdiff</i> = <span style='color: green;'>0.01</span>,
    <i>args</i> = 'list'('peak_method' = 'CentWave', 'snr_threshold' = 3, 'window_half_width' = 5, 'min_peak_width' = 3, 'max_peak_width' = 30, 'min_peak_height' = 0, 'centWave_min_scale' = 1, 'centWave_max_scale' = 20, 'centWave_scale_step' = 1, 'centWave_max_gap' = 2, 'matched_filter_sigma' = 3, 'matched_filter_truncate_width' = 4, 'derivative_smooth_window' = 3, 'derivative_threshold_factor' = 0.01, 'noise_segment_count' = 20, 'peak_merge_distance' = 1, 'area_method' = 'BaselineCorrected', 'baseline_method' = 'Linear', 'baseline_percentile' = 10, 'local_minimum_boundary_points' = 5, 'gaussian_max_iterations' = 100, 'gaussian_convergence' = 1E-06, 'recalculate_snr' = TRUE),
    <i>simple</i> = <span style='color: blue !important;'>TRUE</span>,
    <i>n.threads</i> = <span style='color: green;'>32</span>,
    <i>tmp.out</i> = <span style='color: brown;'><strong>'./tmp'</strong></span>)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fIms1_peaktable(files, mzbins,
    <i>mzdiff</i> = <span style='color: green;'>0.01</span>,
    <i>args</i> = 'list'('peak_method' = 'CentWave', 'snr_threshold' = 3, 'window_half_width' = 5, 'min_peak_width' = 3, 'max_peak_width' = 30, 'min_peak_height' = 0, 'centWave_min_scale' = 1, 'centWave_max_scale' = 20, 'centWave_scale_step' = 1, 'centWave_max_gap' = 2, 'matched_filter_sigma' = 3, 'matched_filter_truncate_width' = 4, 'derivative_smooth_window' = 3, 'derivative_threshold_factor' = 0.01, 'noise_segment_count' = 20, 'peak_merge_distance' = 1, 'area_method' = 'BaselineCorrected', 'baseline_method' = 'Linear', 'baseline_percentile' = 10, 'local_minimum_boundary_points' = 5, 'gaussian_max_iterations' = 100, 'gaussian_convergence' = 1E-06, 'recalculate_snr' = TRUE),
    <i>simple</i> = <span style='color: blue !important;'>TRUE</span>,
    <i>n.threads</i> = <span style='color: green;'>32</span>,
    <i>tmp.out</i> = <span style='color: brown;'><strong>'./tmp'</strong></span>)\fR
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fBfiles\fB \fR\- . a character vector of the file path of the XIC rawdata files
.PP
.PP
\fBmzbins\fB \fR\- . A dataframe object that contains the target ion m/z feature
set for do extract of the result peaktable data, a data field which is
named ``mz`` must be included inside this dataframe object.
.PP
.PP
\fBmzdiff\fB \fR\- 0.01. 
.PP
.PP
\fBargs\fB \fR\- 'list'('peak_method' = 'CentWave', 'snr_threshold' = 3, 'window_half_width' = 5, 'min_peak_width' = 3, 'max_peak_width' = 30, 'min_peak_height' = 0, 'centWave_min_scale' = 1, 'centWave_max_scale' = 20, 'centWave_scale_step' = 1, 'centWave_max_gap' = 2, 'matched_filter_sigma' = 3, 'matched_filter_truncate_width' = 4, 'derivative_smooth_window' = 3, 'derivative_threshold_factor' = 0.01, 'noise_segment_count' = 20, 'peak_merge_distance' = 1, 'area_method' = 'BaselineCorrected', 'baseline_method' = 'Linear', 'baseline_percentile' = 10, 'local_minimum_boundary_points' = 5, 'gaussian_max_iterations' = 100, 'gaussian_convergence' = 1E-06, 'recalculate_snr' = TRUE). 
.PP
.PP
\fBsimple\fB \fR\- TRUE. 
.PP
.PP
\fBn.threads\fB \fR\- 32. 
.PP
.PP
\fBtmp.out\fB \fR\- './tmp'. 
.PP
.SH VALUE
.PP
this function generates a xcms format liked peaktable dataframe object
for the input rawdata files.
.PP
.SH FILES
.PP
SMRUCC/R#.declare_function.ms1_peaktable at ms1_peaktable.R:line 14
.PP
